text:
Corlears Hook Park: The northwest corner of same, as viewed northward on Jackson Street (western boundary of Park) from South Street. Appearing on the right is St. Rose's Home, at the N.W. corner of Jackson and Front Streets. Buildings seen across the Park are on the north side of Cherry Street, between Jackson and Corlears Streets.

April 16, 1928.

P. L. Sperr.
